{"ts":1770040388882,"data":[{"idPlayer":"34177875","idTeam":"133623","idTeam2":"135981","idTeamNational":null,"idAPIfootball":"138822","idPlayerManager":null,"idWikidata":"Q87347516","idTransferMkt":"571743","idESPN":"291535","strNationality":"Albania","strPlayer":"Armando Broja","strPlayerAlternate":"","strTeam":"Burnley","strTeam2":"Albania","strSport":"Soccer","intSoccerXMLTeamID":null,"dateBorn":"2001-09-10","dateDied":null,"strNumber":"27","dateSigned":null,"strSigning":"£20m","strWage":"","strOutfitter":"","strKit":"","strAgent":"","strBirthLocation":"Slough, England","strEthnicity":"","strStatus":"Active","strDescriptionEN":"Armando Broja (born 10 September 2001) is a professional footballer who plays as a striker for Premier League side Burnley. Born in England, he plays for the Albania national team. \r\n\r\nClub career\r\nChelsea\r\nOn 26 February 2020, Broja signed his first professional contract with Premier League side Chelsea after agreeing to a two-year deal. On 8 March 2020, he made his professional debut in a 4–0 home win against Everton after coming on as a substitute in the 86th minute in place of Olivier Giroud.\r\n\r\nOn 18 July 2021, Broja signed a new five-year contract with the club.\r\n\r\nVitesse (loan)\r\nOn 21 August 2020, Broja signed for Vitesse on a season-long loan. On 19 September 2020, he scored his first ever league goal in a 2–0 win over Sparta Rotterdam. Broja finished his loan spell at Vitesse as their joint-top scorer in the Eredivisie for the 2020–21 season, netting ten goals.\r\n\r\nSouthampton (loan)\r\nOn 10 August 2021, Broja was loaned to fellow Premier League club Southampton for the 2021–22 season. On his debut on 25 August, he scored two goals in an emphatic 8–0 win over League Two side Newport County in the second round of the EFL Cup.\r\n\r\nInternational career\r\nUnder-19\r\nOn 28 May 2019, Broja received a call-up from Albania U19 for the friendly matches against Kosovo U19. On 3 June 2019, Broja made his debut with Albania in the first friendly match against Kosovo after being named in the starting line-up and scored his side's third goal during a 3–1 away win.\r\n\r\nUnder-21\r\nOn 9 June 2019, Broja made his debut with Albania U21 in the friendly match against Wales U21 after coming on as a substitute in the 46th minute in place of Din Sula and scored his side's two goals during a 2–1 home win.\r\n\r\nSenior\r\nOn 21 May 2019, Broja received a call-up from Albania for a training camp in Durrës, Albania from 21–26 May 2019.\r\n\r\nOn 7 September 2020 he made his debut in a 1–0 home loss against Lithuania.\r\n\r\nPersonal life\r\nBroja was born in Slough, England to Albanian parents from Malësia e Madhe, Albania.","strDescriptionDE":null,"strDescriptionFR":null,"strDescriptionCN":null,"strDescriptionIT":null,"strDescriptionJP":null,"strDescriptionRU":null,"strDescriptionES":null,"strDescriptionPT":null,"strDescriptionSE":null,"strDescriptionNL":null,"strDescriptionHU":null,"strDescriptionNO":null,"strDescriptionIL":null,"strDescriptionPL":null,"strGender":"Male","strSide":"","strPosition":"Centre-Forward","strCollege":null,"strFacebook":"","strWebsite":"","strTwitter":"","strInstagram":"","strYoutube":"","strHeight":"1.91 m (6 ft 3 in)","strWeight":"183 lbs","intLoved":"0","strThumb":"https://r2.thesportsdb.com/images/media/player/thumb/ijard31630183333.jpg","strPoster":null,"strCutout":"https://r2.thesportsdb.com/images/media/player/cutout/op1eh71757174345.png","strCartoon":null,"strRender":"https://r2.thesportsdb.com/images/media/player/render/p27p4l1630183413.png","strBanner":null,"strFanart1":null,"strFanart2":null,"strFanart3":null,"strFanart4":null,"strCreativeCommons":"Yes","strLocked":"unlocked","strLastName":"Broja"},{"idPlayer":"34146052","idTeam":"133623","idTeam2":null,"idTeamNational":null,"idAPIfootball":"18927","idPlayerManager":null,"idWikidata":"Q725747","idTransferMkt":"63200","idESPN":"105405","strNationality":"Austria","strPlayer":"Ashley Barnes","strPla